# Contributing to Jino OS

Thanks for interested in Jino OS v3.1 Hybrid!

## Quick start

```bash
git clone https://github.com/yourusername/JinoOS.git
cd JinoOS
python3 tools/jino_console.py
# Select language 1) EN
# help
# gui --browser # opens browser GUI
```

Open `emulator/index.html` in browser for Windows-like GUI + Console hybrid.

## Project structure

```
JinoOS/
├── tools/jino_console.py      # Main OS - Python console + server manager + curl + errors + gui launcher
├── lang/en.json, ru.json      # Language files
├── packages/repo.json         # 18 server packages repo
├── emulator/index.html        # Hybrid Windows-like GUI + Terminal (console alive)
├── emulator/console_server.html # Pure console server edition
├── src/boot/boot.asm          # Bootloader 16->32 bit
├── src/kernel/                # JinoKernel C
├── src/drivers/               # VGA, keyboard
├── src/shell/                 # JinoSH
├── src/gui/                   # JinoWM Window Manager v3.1 Hybrid (console remains)
├── src/fullstack/             # JinoDB, JinoServer
├── docs/                      # SERVERS.md, CURL.md, ERRORS.md, architecture.md
├── LICENSE                    # MIT - easy permissive
├── README.md                  # GitHub README
└── Makefile
```

## How to add feature

1. Fork repo
2. Create branch: `git checkout -b feature/my-feature`
3. Edit `tools/jino_console.py` for console logic, or `emulator/index.html` for GUI
4. Test: `python3 tools/jino_console.py` -> `jpkg list`, `srv quick nginx`, `curl http://localhost:8080/`, `errors`, `lang ru`, `gui`
5. Commit: `git commit -m "Add my feature"`
6. PR

## Code style

- Console: Keep console primary, GUI optional - never remove console!
- Language: Default EN, support EN/RU via `lang/` and `t()` function
- Errors: Always use `print_error("JNO-XXX", context, extra)` with full explanation
- Servers: Use ServerManager, real ThreadingHTTPServer on 127.0.0.1, not just simulation
- GUI: Windows-like but console alive inside Terminal app

## Adding server package

Edit `packages/repo.json`:
```json
{
  "name": "myserver",
  "version": "1.0",
  "description": "My cool server",
  "type": "server",
  "port": 8888,
  "root": "/www/myserver"
}
```
Then `jpkg list` will show it.

## Adding language

Create `lang/<code>.json` copy of en.json and translate. Then `lang <code>` will work.

